      "description": "Available is a 2004 Porsche 911 Carrera, a driver-focused 996.2 featuring the 3.6L M96 flat-six engine. This unit is mechanically robust, highlighted by a documented IMS bearing retrofit and a recently replaced Rear Main Seal (RMS). The 6-speed G96 manual transaxle provides precise gate engagement, and the chassis remains balanced with Bilstein B6 dampers and refreshed control arm bushings. The naturally aspirated powerplant delivers linear torque through the rev range, maintaining excellent compression across all cylinders. While the exterior shows minor road-going patina, the internals\u2014including the VarioCam Plus system\u2014function flawlessly. This is a high-utility example for the purist who values visceral feedback and rear-engine kinematics over a garage-queen status.",
